gr.alieus.lib6.collect

Interface DequeMap<K,V>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedDequeHashMap

    public interface DequeMap<K,V>
    Data structure that maps a key to multiple values.

    The values of each key work as a deque (double ended queue). Meaning, they can be operated upon as a stack or as a queue. Additionally, the API of the DequeMap is designed in a way that it can be treated as a regular, single-valued, map.

    A key is considered to exist in the map if at least one value is associated with it.

      • addAll

        void addAll(K key,
            Collection<? extends V> values)
        Adds all the values of the given collection as the first values of the given key in the order they are returned by the collections iterator.

        The effect of this call is not equivalent to that of calling add(K, V) for each element of the given collection since add would insert each value to the front causing the collection to be added in reverse order.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to which the values will be added
        values - the values to add
